  <!-- OVERVIEW -->
  <section class="case-section">
    <p class="section-label">The Work</p>
    <h2 class="section-heading">Turning research into a prioritized investment framework</h2>
    <div class="case-body">
      <p>This presentation represents the second phase of Highmark's behavioral health innovation initiative — moving from problem definition to opportunity prioritization. After extensive research with patients, clinicians, providers, and payers, the team identified and developed a set of specific, actionable opportunities Highmark could pursue to address systemic barriers to BH care.</p>
      <p>Each opportunity was mapped against impact and effort, supported by competitive landscape analysis, framed with "How Might We" questions, and scoped with priority recommendations for next steps and ownership. The work was designed to directly inform Highmark's long-term BH investment strategy.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

